    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for mod_proxy_cluster.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 10.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The mod_proxy_cluster module is a plugin for the Apache HTTP Server that provides load-balancer functionality.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* mod_proxy_cluster: mod_proxy_cluster unauthorized MCMP requests (CVE-2024-10306)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
